<span id="freeTextContainer10991454266677445046">“…and there was a thick darkness in all the land of Egypt three days: They saw not one another, neither rose any from his place for three days…” <i>Exodus 10:22-23</i><br/>The battle of good and evil is everlasting… and there are no winners. And at times it is hard to decide which is which.<br/><i>Darkness Visible</i> is complex and multilevel and the mazes of human mind are like gaols.<br/><blockquote>We&apos;re all mad, the whole damned race. We&apos;re wrapped in illusions, delusions, confusions about the penetrability of partitions, we&apos;re al</blockquote></span>
  <span id="freeText10991454266677445046" style="display:none">“…and there was a thick darkness in all the land of Egypt three days: They saw not one another, neither rose any from his place for three days…” <i>Exodus 10:22-23</i><br />The battle of good and evil is everlasting… and there are no winners. And at times it is hard to decide which is which.<br /><i>Darkness Visible</i> is complex and multilevel and the mazes of human mind are like gaols.<br /><blockquote>We're all mad, the whole damned race. We're wrapped in illusions, delusions, confusions about the penetrability of partitions, we're all mad and in solitary confinement.</blockquote><br />The human destiny is the eternal biblical struggle with the darkness without and with the darkness within.</span>
