<div id="review_10630005" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/10630005" />
    <a title="Derrick" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/603055-derrick"><img alt="Derrick" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1204831837p2/603055.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/10630005?book_show_action=true">Dec 18, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Derrick" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Derrick" href="/user/show/603055-derrick">Derrick</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer10630005" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer525360250341810268">I love Golding&apos;s view of the world. This continues where &quot;Lord of the Flies&quot; left off; that human nature is inherently savage. That is, the world isn&apos;t needed to corrupt a child, we all accomplish that just fine on our own. Bleak, but intriguing. This book was also clever and suspenseful, more so than LotF, excellent read.</span>
  <span id="freeText525360250341810268" style="display:none">I love Golding's view of the world. This continues where "Lord of the Flies" left off; that human nature is inherently savage. That is, the world isn't needed to corrupt a child, we all accomplish that just fine on our own. Bleak, but intriguing. This book was also clever and suspenseful, more so than LotF, excellent read.</span>
  <a data-text-id="525360250341810268" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


